      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "This memo outlines the firm's obligations under the GDPR, identifying itself as the Data Controller and requiring the client to engage a Data Processor for all technical services. We must ensure all Personal Data, including Special Categories of Data, is collected only with valid Consent, adhering to the principles of Purpose Limitation, Data Minimization, and Storage Limitation. Furthermore, the client must implement Privacy by Design and maintain robust Security of Processing to guarantee the Integrity and Confidentiality of all records.\n\nTo satisfy our Accountability requirements, the client is obligated to conduct a Data Protection Impact Assessment for high-risk processing and must establish clear procedures for Breach Notification and Cross-Border Data Transfers. Finally, the system must respect the Rights of the Data Subject, including the Right to Erasure and the ability to withdraw Consent at any time, while avoiding unlawful Automated Decision-Making. This framework ensures full Transparency and meets all key regulatory mandates for compliance.",
      "source": "target",
