      "content": "This memo establishes the firm's role as the Data Controller, obligating the client to engage Data Processors who must strictly adhere to Security of Processing and Integrity and Confidentiality standards to protect all Personal Data and Special Categories of Data. Operational compliance requires implementing Privacy by Design and Data Minimization, ensuring that data collection is limited to what is necessary for the specific Purpose Limitation and that Storage Limitation protocols are enforced to prevent unnecessary retention.\n\nTo fulfill Accountability obligations, the client must conduct Data Protection Impact Assessments for high-risk activities and maintain documented evidence of these measures to demonstrate Transparency to regulators and stakeholders. In the event of a Breach Notification, the client must report incidents within 72 hours to the supervisory authority, while simultaneously notifying affected Data Subjects unless the risk is minimal.\n\nRegarding Data Subject Rights, the system must facilitate the Right to Erasure and Consent Withdrawal without undue delay, and any Automated Decision-Making processes must be human-supervised to avoid legal violations. Finally, all Cross-Border Data Transfers require appropriate safeguards to ensure continued protection of data across jurisdictions, thereby finalizing a robust compliance framework.",
